==Bosnian==

===Etymology===
From Turkish [[alet#Turkish|alet]] < Arabic {{ARchar|'''الات'''}} plural of {{ARchar|[[الة|آلَة]]}} (''instrument'').

===Noun===
'''alat''' {{m}} ''collective'' ({{s}}: '''alatka''', {{p}} {{m}}: '''alati''', {{p}} {{f}}: '''alatke''')

#[[tool]]s
#[[instrument]]s

==Usage notes==
When used collectively, the word is masculine.  However, when used as a singular, the word is feminine.  But, when used as a plural, the word can be either masculine or feminine.''

===Alternative spellings===
*[[halat#Bosnian|halat]] (''poetic'')

